How to Use the N8n Workflow Explainer Skill
What This Skill Does
It takes your n8n workflow summaries (which you upload into the skill), picks the one you choose, reads the full workflow logic, and writes a step-by-step breakdown formatted for LinkedIn posts, Instagram carousels, or Instagram feed posts.
It's a content generation tool for technical workflows — not a workflow builder.
Step 1: Install the Skill
Download the skill .zip file from the provided link
Do not unzip it
In Claude, go to Customize → Skills
Click the + icon → Upload a Skill
Upload the .zip file as-is
Done
Step 2: Add Your Workflow Summaries to the Skill
Before using the skill, your n8n workflow summaries must be inside the skill file. These are pre-uploaded descriptions of each workflow you want to turn into content.
The skill comes with example workflows already inside. To add your own, include them in the skill folder before uploading.
Step 3: Invoke the Skill
Type the skill name or ask anything about workflow content creation. Claude triggers the skill automatically.
The skill lists all available workflows inside it. Example: if you have 2 workflows uploaded, it shows both. You pick one.
Step 4: Answer 2 Quick Questions
Question 1: Who is your target ICP?
Name the exact person you're writing for. Example: CMOs at SaaS companies
Question 2: Any specific numbers, context, or details to include?
Add real data — campaign results, time saved, client outcomes. If you have nothing to add, type "na" and move on.
Step 5: Receive the Draft
Claude reads the full workflow file for your chosen workflow and outputs a complete step-by-step breakdown structured for social content:
Each step of the workflow explained in plain language
Formatted for LinkedIn post or Instagram carousel/feed
Written for the ICP you specified
Step 6: Edit the Draft — 3 Things You Can Change
The skill flags this at the end of the draft itself. Three levers:
1. Change the angle
The default angle is the workflow itself. You can reframe it. Example: "Replace the VA angle with: I run this before every outbound campaign"
2. Hit a specific pain point
If you want to lead with a particular problem your ICP has, tell Claude exactly which pain point to center the post around.
3. Change the desired outcome
What should the reader walk away believing or doing? Change this if the default doesn't match your goal for the post.
The Core Rule
The output quality depends entirely on the quality of the workflow summaries you put inside the skill. Vague workflow descriptions = vague step-by-step content. Detailed workflow summaries with real logic = content that actually teaches something.
