How to Use the Offer Clarity Framework Skill
Build a solid, specific offer you can actually use in cold outreach and content
What is this skill and why does it exist?
Most offers are vague. "We help companies grow revenue." "We build systems that save time." These mean nothing to a prospect, and they definitely won't convert in a cold email.
The Offer Clarity Framework skill forces you to think through your offer at a structural level — who it's for, what exact problem it solves, what the outcome looks like, and what objections will kill the deal. The output is a full offer document you can use as the foundation for cold email copy, LinkedIn content, sales calls, or your website positioning.
This is not a one-click magic output. You feed it real inputs, Claude asks follow-up questions, and then you push back, iterate, and make the output sharper. That's the process.
Before You Start
If you've already used the ICP Problem Desire Finder skill, pull up that output document. This skill takes your ICP psychographic details as one of its inputs. If you haven't run the Desire Finder yet, you can still proceed — but your output will be less sharp. The two skills work best together.
